{"type": "root", "attrs": {"type": "node", "context": "cop", "internal": "rasterizesetup", "icon": "COP/rasterizesetup", "version": null, "namespace": null}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Rasterize Setup"], "extent": [88, 108]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Prepares geometry for the Rasterize Geometry COP."], "extent": [108, 166]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This node performs common preparations to setup geometry for the\n", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes//cop/rasterizegeo", "type": "link", "text": ["Rasterize Geometry COP"], "fullpath": "/nodes//cop/rasterizegeo.html"}, ".  Since the default camera for layers is a\nunit-radius cube at the origin, it is important to fit and align\ngeometry so it renders as expected."], "extent": [166, 425]}, {"level": 1, "id": "parameters", "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [425, 437], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Space"], "extent": [437, 445], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["What space to render in.  Rather than having the rasterize\n    geometry unwrap, this can unwrap into UV space so you can verify\n    it is correct in the viewport before rasterization."], "extent": [461, 654]}, {"type": "dt_group", "body": [{"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Position"], "extent": [654, 668], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Use ", {"type": "code", "text": ["P"]}, ", which is the geometry as it is."], "extent": [668, 735]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["UVs"], "extent": [735, 744], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Unwrap the geometry into a UV space.  This involves splitting\n        the polygons along UV seams, copying UV onto P, and then\n        re-fitting the 0 to 1 UV space to the -1 to 1 camera space."], "extent": [744, 961]}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "space"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Orientation"], "extent": [961, 974], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The default camera is to look down the Z-axis with Y-up. You can switch to Z-up if you want a top-down rasterization."], "extent": [991, 1118]}, {"type": "dt_group", "body": [{"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Y-Up"], "extent": [1118, 1128], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Leave the geometry unchanged so the default cameras render\n        Y-up."], "extent": [1128, 1218]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Z-Up"], "extent": [1218, 1228], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Rotate the geometry so the original Z axis points up, and the\n        original Y-axis points with the camera."], "extent": [1228, 1360]}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "orient"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Fit From"], "extent": [1360, 1370], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The incoming geometry can be fit into the camera space."], "extent": [1384, 1449]}, {"type": "dt_group", "body": [{"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["No Fitting"], "extent": [1449, 1465], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Do not adjust the spacing of the geoemtry."], "extent": [1465, 1525]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Bounding Box"], "extent": [1525, 1543], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Use the bounding box of the geometry as the source shape to\n        fit."], "extent": [1543, 1633]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Reference Box"], "extent": [1633, 1652], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Use a specific reference size as the source shape to fit. This\n        is useful if you have an animated source to fit and do not\n        want fitting to change every frame, or want to ignore\n        ascenders or descenders."], "extent": [1652, 1899]}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "fit"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Reference Size"], "extent": [1899, 1915], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The size of the reference box to fit into the target box."], "extent": [1932, 2004]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "refsize"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Reference Position"], "extent": [2004, 2024], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The center of the reference box to fit into the target box."], "extent": [2040, 2114]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "refpos"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Target Position"], "extent": [2114, 2131], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The center of the target box to fit to."], "extent": [2150, 2204]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "targetpos"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Target Size"], "extent": [2204, 2217], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The size of the target box to fit to."], "extent": [2237, 2289]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "targetsize"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Scale to Fit"], "extent": [2289, 2303], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Apply a uniform scale to fit to the target box.  Otherwise only a\n    translation will be done."], "extent": [2321, 2427]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "doscale"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Fit Depth"], "extent": [2427, 2438], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["You may wish to auto-squash the depth of your geometry to a given\n    bounds without affecting the other axes.  This specifies what\n    range the resulting geometry should extend over."], "extent": [2457, 2656]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "fitdepth"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["UV Attribute"], "extent": [2656, 2670], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The attribute to use for UV unwrapping.  This can be vertex or\n    point."], "extent": [2689, 2777]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "uvattrib"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Add Normals If Needed"], "extent": [2777, 2800], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Computes normals if none are present. The Rasterize Geometry\n    COP does not compute missing normals, so this is important if\n    pipelining variable geometry."], "extent": [2820, 2990]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "addnormal"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Add Depth"], "extent": [2990, 3001], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Add a depth attribute of this name.  This can be rasterized to get\n    a normalized ", {"type": "code", "text": ["1"]}, " to ", {"type": "code", "text": ["0"]}, " depth, where ", {"type": "code", "text": ["1"]}, " is closest to the camera\n    and ", {"type": "code", "text": ["0"]}, " the farthest.  This tends to be a useful setup for\n    masks, as opposed to the true depth which can have more difficult\n    to work with ranges."], "extent": [3023, 3332]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "depthattrib"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Original Position"], "extent": [3332, 3351], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The original position, prior to unwrapping or fitting, is stashed\n    into this attribute.  This allows one to rasterize the original\n    positions."], "extent": [3373, 3536]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "origpattrib"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "text": "Parameters"}, {"level": 1, "id": "inputs", "container": true, "type": "inputs_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [3536, 3544], "body": [{"type": "dt_group", "body": [{"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["source"], "extent": [3544, 3556], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["The geometry to prepare for rasterization."], "extent": [3556, 3608]}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "text": "Inputs"}, {"level": 1, "id": "outputs", "container": true, "type": "outputs_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [3608, 3617], "body": [{"type": "dt_group", "body": [{"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["result"], "extent": [3617, 3629], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["The geometry that is setup for rasterization."], "extent": [3629, 3684]}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "text": "Outputs"}, {"level": 1, "id": "related", "container": true, "type": "related_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [3684, 3693], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/cop/rasterizegeo", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/cop/rasterizegeo.html"}], "extent": [3693, 3720]}], "container": true}], "text": "Related"}], "title": ["Rasterize Setup"], "summary": ["Prepares geometry for the Rasterize Geometry COP."]}